description: Robin investigates a bizarre coincidence - two guys with exactly the same features involved in violent attacks in the same day. When he checks the police reports, he discovers that there are even more of these incidents, and when he runs the face through a criminal database, it matches Drury Walker, formerly Killer Moth and now Charaxes. He heads to the area where the homeless have been reporting a monster killing numerous people, and discovers something quite repulsive - Charaxes appears to be hatching a brood of mini Drury Walkers in an abandoned building. Nightwing is on his way to help him out, but before he can, Charaxes discovers Robin's presence...
name: Snack Time!

description:
As Clark Kent and Lois Lane move into their new apartment, Clark reminisces about his times in Smallville. In particular, his memories turn to Kenny Braverman, a friend who always came in second behind Clark. Little does Clark know that Kenny has now become the super-villain Conduit, and is gunning for Clark. Clark has won a Baldy Award, and Conduit has set up a bomb at the awards ceremony. Luckily, Superman has come in to save the day, rescuing everyone at the awards. Superman defeats Conduit’s agents that continue the assault, but does not discover who is behind the attempt on Clark’s life. When Clark returns to his apartment, he finds his photo with a knife through it attached to his door. Now, Clark is sure someone is gunning for him as Clark Kent, not Superman.

Notes:

  • On page 5 panel 2 Clark Kent has a Captain Action action figure.
  • A Zero Hour crossover issue.
  • Triangle 1994 #38.
  • Chronological continuation from Superman: The Man of Steel #0.
  • Chronological continuation in Adventures of Superman #0.
name: Peer Pressure Part 2: Awards

description: Kal Kent, Superman from the 853rd Century saves Roy Harper from Vandal Savage's Rocket Red suit, which had been set on auto pilot to detonate in Metropolis, and programmed to defend it self from any opposition. A mob, driven mad by the Hourman Virus, mistrusts and attacks him, but Roy and the local authorities hold them off while Kal meets up with Lois Lane and they search for components to build a solar computer to contain the virus. Lex Luthor offers assistance but ultimately betrays them, as he too is affected by the Hourman Virus. Even though Kal's powers are fading one by one in the absence of the Super Sun of his era, he defeats Luthor's armored guards and escapes with Lois. Having failed to find the parts he needs and unable to enter the Fortress of Solitude, he resolves to go to the JLA Watchtower on the Moon.
name: Down To Earth

description:
'Nuff Said story with no text.

Wolverine vs. Mauvais vs. the Wendigo! Logan's in a fight for his life against the macabre man who tore out his eye and the flesh-eating man trapped in the body of an insatiable Canadian monster! This one could get really ugly! But why is Logan trying to save the Wendigo's life at the same time? Plus: What's Sabretooth up to? The action is so intense no one has time to breathe, much less to speak in this silent brawl-for-it-all!
name: Stay Alive! Part 2 Of 3
The Case of the Hired Gunman
